ions of the GIMME. A total of\nthree isobaric quintets have their most exotic members measured by Penning trap\nmass spectrometry. The GIMME predictions in the $T = 2$ quintet appear to break\ndown for $A = 32$ and greater.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 6 May 2020 19:37:14 GMT"}],"update_date":"2021-02-03"}
